    {
      "id": "9bd499c4c675a842b976251ab525370b45a09db4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-08-05 19:05:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 6: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nIs this patch already in use in production systems using this OBD_CONNECT value?  This conflicts with the value that was recently reserved for nanosecond timestamps. If it IS in production use already, we will need to change the value for the nanosecond timestamp feature, but I would not be terribly happy in this case. It would be a terribly bad idea to use OBD_CONNECT values in production that were not already reserved in master and b1_8 first to avoid conflicts.\n\nAs for the patch itself, I need to take a closer look at the interaction between this patch and the others related to flock when I'm back from vacation tomorrow and not looking at it on my phone. I though that there was already a compatibility mechanism in place for this problem with the flock owner, but I don't recall the details without looking at the code and old patches.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 6
    },
    {
      "id": "4f0b5c6778532a275d1840a53c01563812109de4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 190,
        "name": "Iurii Golovach",
        "email": "Iurii_Golovach@xyratex.com",
        "username": "Iurii",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-08-15 13:09:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\nHi Andreas,\n\nI've nothing against to change the OBD_CONNECT value on new one.\n\nJust let me know if this only one request and you finished your review and I'll provide a patch with updated value.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 6
    },
